column5: Looking to start a network of Anglers who live, cottage or fish regularly on Dalrymple. Share tips, patterns and trends to help each other have productive fishing experiences.
I am on Daly every weekend from May to October!
I fished Dalrymple a half dozen times or so last year.
you can also try http://www.kawarthaanglers.com/forum - they have a board on daly.
I also fished the lake every week-end for 21 years and still have a trailer there. My pattern for this year will be to try and follow Gord around the lake! I don't mind "sloppy seconds"! LOL
Hey Brian if you want to catch something you might want to follow someone who knows what they are doing I`m still trying to figure that lake out.
I've heard that there's a few fish in there, I may have to head up and check it out this year.  It's been a while, right Brian.
Usually get up 3-4 times a year.  Easy lake to figure out, really.
Yes Chris...too long. Let's set a date and i will do all the work so you can rest your back! Deal?

Last time I fished Daly,it was during a BASS tourny. Buddy fished shallow,I threw tubes to the deep end. Guess who caught fish?  Great bass lake. Brian or lookinforwalleye , Im up for a day or two on the lake with yas.Just shoot a pm.
Hey Brian anytime,Brian and I have trailers in the same park it would be great to have a couple of Off`ners up for a fish, burger and a beer!!!

Yeah Gord, Lets make this happen this year. I have fished with Misfish in his boat, but never had the chance to return the favour. Layzee Acres was the first place I met Spiel as well, but we have never shared a boat together yet. For that matter, WE have not even fished together! LOL
Sounds good we`ll leave the wife`s at home one weekend and have boys weekend!!!
